places.perex: This scenic course is well-cared for and one of the best on the islands. Fantastic views and a pleasant game.

places.name: Valley Church Beach
places.perex: A pleasant beach often used by the locals for fishing and lounging in the sun. There is a restaurant here, so you can easily spend the day.

places.name: Fig Tree Drive
places.perex: A beautiful scenic drive through one of the lush areas of Antigua. Look out for the sights along the way, some of them are worth a visit.

places.name: Jolly Harbour Golf Club
places.perex: 18 holes, par 71. A shorter course that provides challenges due to the water hazards present here. Nice scenery.

places.name: Sheer Rocks

places.perex: Spanish Point is, along with nearby Coco Point, one of the two southernmost points on the Caribbean island of Barbuda.

places.name: Palmetto Point
places.perex: Palmetto Point is a prominent headland that marks the southeasternmost point of the Caribbean island of Barbuda.

places.name: Cades Reef
places.perex: A fun dive site for both beginners and experienced divers. Plethora of Caribbean marine life shows up here.

places.name: Pepperz N' Lime
places.perex: Authentic Mexican restaurant great for lunches, dinners and late-night drinks. A friendly establishment with live DJ music.

places.name: Sugar Club
places.perex: A lively restaurant, bar and spa. Stop by for one of the themed nights or get yourself pampered with one of the spa treatments.

places.name: La Bussola Restaurant
places.perex: An upscale Italian restaurant sporting a great location, delicious dishes and good service. Great for special occasions.

places.name: Abracadabra
places.perex: Delicious Italian cuisine in a beautiful Victorian setting. Serves as one of the best discos on the island.

places.name: Runaway Beach
places.perex: A small but marvellous beach with facilities to sustain you throughout the day. Popular with windsurfers in the winter.

places.name: Greencastle Hill
places.perex: Not just a good hike with nice views - there are mysterious megaliths  left here by the indigenous people of the islands.

places.name: Long Bay
places.perex: A serene beach not completely stripped off facilities. Perfect for spending the day simply lounging under the trees.

places.name: Frigate Bird Sanctuary
places.perex: This spread-out sanctuary is home to dozens of frigate birds and gives you a chance to get really close to them - do not miss it.

places.name: Fort Berkeley
places.perex: The fort used to protect a nearby natural harbour. Nowadays it is a captivating historical site with beautiful scenery surrounding it.

places.name: Dutchman's Bay
places.perex: A quiet and secluded beach - perfect if you need some privacy. There is one restaurant, so you can easily spend the day here.

places.name: Indian Town National Park
places.perex: A small park that nonetheless offers dozens of hiking opportunities along the lush greenery. Worth a visit.

places.name: 17-Mile Beach
places.perex: The longest beach of the Caribbean that is often completely deserted. Seventeen miles of unspoilt, picture perfect beauty.

places.name: Monks Hill
places.perex: The hike up this hill isn't too demanding and offers great views of the harbour underneath and its azure waters.

places.name: Pillars of Hercules
places.perex: An interesting geological formation - but the main sight is under the sea. Great snorkelling and diving location.

places.name: Dow's Hill Interpretation Centre
places.perex: Learn about Antiguan history in this brief 20-minute show. Housed in an old fort and with great views of the island.

places.name: Harmony Hall
places.perex: Doubles as a restaurant and art gallery. Showcases artwork made by local artists and serves mostly seafood.

places.name: Hawksbill Bay
places.perex: There are several beaches for you to choose from - all are beautiful and rarely get cluttered with seaweed.

places.name: Half Moon Bay
places.perex: This picturesque bay has two faces. The north is favoured by snorkellers, while the south is a great spot for windsurfing.

places.name: Dark Wood Beach
places.perex: A lovely beach with some facilities to sustain you through the day. Great for enjoying the sea, snorkelling and beachcombing.

places.name: Galley Bay Beach
places.perex: A marvellous, well-facilitated beach where you could easily spend the whole day. The sea can get a little rough here.

places.name: Wallings Forest & Reservoir
places.perex: The picturesque Victorian dam is surrounded by lush evergreen forest. Hiking around here is rewarding and you might even see rare birds.

places.name: Two Foot Bay
places.perex: Not just a beach, but also a national park where the azure sea contrasts with brown cliffs. Get a guide and explore the local caves.

places.name: Bumpkins
places.perex: This beachside bar has a long tradition with both the locals and visitors. Serves great Caribbean-inspired food too.

places.name: Palaster Reef
places.perex: Snorkelling and diving are both popular on this reef which is rich on marine life and dotted with shipwrecks. A hidden gem.

places.name: The Andes
places.perex: The bay was apparently deep enough for this merchant ship to sink 100 years ago. One of the island's diving sites.

places.name: Highland House
places.perex: Ruins of an 18th-century home on the highest point of the island. Offers spectacular views and exploration opportunities.

places.name: Darby's Cave
places.perex: Not a cave, but a large sinkhole. Known for the surrounding nature, the birds that live here and the rock formations.

places.name: Access Beach
places.perex: This vast beach stretching on forever is a great spot for almost any beach activity, be it swimming or picnicking.

places.name: Mosquito Cove Beach
places.perex: The drive here might be bumpy, but the lovely scenery and tranquil beach more than make up for it. Beware of the mosquitoes after dark.

places.name: Coco Point
places.perex: This gorgeous beach is one of the most beautiful in the Caribbean. Pinkish sand, azure sea and nobody around - what more to wish for?

places.name: Martello Tower
places.perex: A protective tower left here by the British - there used to be a quay nearby. A navigating point and the best place to go for grand views.

places.name: North Beach
places.perex: Perhaps one of the most serene and charming beaches in the Caribbean. There is a resort here that can cater to your needs.

places.name: Palm Beach
places.perex: Twenty-two kilometres of pristine white sands lined with seashells and azure sea. A true beach paradise, although with rarely any shade.
